  "info_title": "About this page",
  "info_description": "**Project Space**\n\nThis is where you can find all of your projects in one place. You can add separate tasks or materials and delete projects.\n\nWhen you open a project, you'll see an overview with:\n\n• Hours already spent\n• Estimated hours for the project\n• Overall progress\n• Other key project details\n\nThe project is organized into **three main tabs:**\n\n**Tasks**\nHere you'll find all tasks assigned to the project, neatly organized into folders.\nYou can update **progress** and **logged hours** directly for each task.\n\n**Materials**\nThis section contains all materials required for the project.\nYou can track **what has been delivered** and **on which day**, keeping full control over material arrivals.\n\n**Equipment**\nHere you can select and request the equipment needed for the project.\n\n**Additional Sections**\nThere are also two smaller sections:\n\n• **Additional Tasks**\n• **Additional Materials**\n\nThese allow you to add tasks or materials that were **not included during the initial project setup** — typically extra work or items that weren't estimated at the beginning.",
  "info_important_note": "**Important:** *Submitting a request does **not** automatically confirm the equipment or materials. Requests are only notifications. Once the equipment or materials are delivered, you must manually confirm and log them in the appropriate section.*",
  "project_management_info_title": "About this page",
  "project_management_info_description": "**Project Management**\n\nThe **Project Performance** section is divided into **four main parts**.\n\n**1. Project Setup & Breakdown**\nThe first part allows you to **create a new project**. The process is intuitive and easy to follow. More information will be shown in the project creating note.\n\n**2. Weekly Workers Hours**\nThis section gives you a clear overview of **employee working hours**.\n\nYou can see:\n\n• Total hours worked by each employee\n• What tasks they worked on during those hours\n\nAll employee entries are automatically summarized here, so you no longer need to check hours day by day — everything is clearly displayed in one place.\n\n**3. Project Performance**\nThis is an analytical overview of the project's progress.\n\nYou can filter data by:\n\n• A specific day\n• A full week\n• Any custom time range\n\nHere you'll see:\n\n• Total hours worked\n• Delivered materials\n• Progress made on the project\n\nThis section is useful both for **internal project tracking** and for **sharing progress with clients**, for example when issuing invoices for a specific week or month.\n(Although detailed financial tools are available separately in the Finance section.)\n\n**4. Removing Records**\nThe final section allows you to **remove incorrect records**.\n\nEmployees can add entries to Task Performance, Additional Materials, and other areas, and mistakes can happen. This page lets you delete incorrect or accidental entries so they don't affect:\n\n• Project statistics\n• Performance tracking\n• Estimated hours for tasks\n\nThis helps keep your project data clean and accurate.",
  "project_creating_info_title": "About this page",
  "project_creating_info_description": "**Project Creating**\n\nYou start by filling in **basic information** such as the project name, description, and start date.\n\nNext, you add **Main Tasks** — these are calculator-based tasks used to estimate all key parameters (time, materials, workload) and assign them directly to the project.\n\nYou'll also find **Minor Tasks**, which are smaller, predefined tasks available to select from a list. This section represents a detailed task breakdown, allowing you to plan work in smaller, more precise steps.\n\nFor example, instead of estimating an entire patio with jointing and finishing, you can add a small task like laying just a few slabs. This gives you full flexibility for minor or additional works.\n\n**Materials**\nAll materials required for Main Tasks are calculated automatically — you don't need to worry about them.\nIn this section, you only add additional materials that are not part of the main task calculations.\n\n**Equipment**\nHere you select the required equipment, such as an excavator and a carrier (dumper, petrol barrow, or wheelbarrow).\n\nBased on your equipment selection and all Main Tasks, the system automatically calculates:\n\n• The amount of soil to be excavated\n• The time needed to excavate and remove it\n\nYou'll also find:\n\n• **Soil Excavation** — with a detailed time calculation (you can manually add extra soil to be removed if needed)\n• **Tape Preparation** — including preparation time and required quantity\n\nFinally, the **Total Results** section provides a complete breakdown of all calculated values for the project.",
